        <num>CC 2023</num>
        <heading>2023.  Security for performance</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2023.  Security for performance
If the situation of a party, financial or otherwise, has become such as to clearly endanger his ability to perform an obligation, the other party may demand in writing that adequate security be given and, upon failure to give that security, that party may withhold or discontinue his own performance.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109281</p>
        </authorialNote>
